The paper deals with distributed algorithms for a combinatorial optimization problem, which suggests that it could belong to the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The problem being studied is the Multiple Knapsack Problem, which is a classic problem in combinatorial optimization and could also place the paper in the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The paper proposes approximation algorithms, which could also place it in the Game Theory (cs.GT) category. Finally, the paper deals with algorithmic techniques, which could place it in the Algorithms (cs.AL) category.
